  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Junior Scientists at Iracambi transforms schoolkids in Brazil&apos;s Atlantic Rainforest into forest guardians. Through hands-on education they learn real science, collecting and monitoring data on soils and water, making, planting and caring for forest seedlings, and sharing their discoveries with their families. Our weekly education program is helping raise a new generation to understand and care for the rainforests that shelter biodiversity, protect water resources and help regulate our climate.</narrative>
  </description>
